<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12053l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12053l">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12053l"> 53(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> lebbra</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Aussi les chemins montais &eacute;taient-ils sillonn&eacute;s par des foules si nombreuses, dit un vieux texte, qu&apos;elles ne pouvaient souvent trouver de provisions. Les malades et les infirmes abondaient; c&apos;est pourquoi, dans un p&eacute;rim&egrave;tre assez &eacute;tendu du Mont Saint-Michel, s&apos;&eacute;taient &eacute;lev&eacute;es des maladreries, des l&eacute;proseries ou des maisons du pauvre. Ces h&ocirc;pitaux g&eacute;n&eacute;ralement tenus par des religieux &eacute;taient presque toujours insuffisants pour y abriter ceux qui en sollicitaient le secours. Les d&eacute;plorables conditions d&apos;hygi&egrave;ne, dans lesquelles vivaient les p&egrave;lerins, contaminaient le pays. La l&egrave;pre, surtout, faisait de terribles ravages et les l&eacute;proseries dans lesquelles on traitait, tant bien que mal les infortun&eacute;s que cette maladie d&eacute;vorait, &eacute;taient toujours remplies. <br><font color="green">[Also the roads of the Mont were trodden by such large crowds, says an old text, that they could not find provisions. Many of them were sick or crippled; that is why, in a quite large circle around Mont-Saint-Michel, hospitals, leproseries and poor houses had been erected. These hospitals, usually administered by clerics, could not shelter all who asked for help. The deplorable hygienic conditions in which the pilgrims live, contaminated the land. Leprosy especially ravaged the land and the leper houses where the unfortunates were treated, for better or worse, were always full.]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="SMIN" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SMIN"><cite title="source">Le Mont Saint-Michel Inconnu</cite></a> (1912) 45</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: It. <i>lebbra</i>: leprosy. </mm> </dd></dl>
